    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-11-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-11-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="138" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                <head>No. 138.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Messrs. <persName type="from">Swift and
                                Trescot</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United
                                    States Commission to China</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-11-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 29,
                            1880</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: By the last dispatches and telegrams from the
                        commission, you were informed that two treaties had been signed, and that
                        Messrs. Swift and Trescot would leave for Shanghai on the 20th, and that Mr.
                        Trescot would bring over the treaties by the first Pacific steamer that he
                        could reach from this point.</p>
                <p>We left Peking on the 20th and reached Shanghai on the 27th. The steamer
                        connecting with the Pacific line at Yokohama leaving on the 30th, Mr.
                        Trescot will go in her to take the City of Peking at that port on the 8th
                        December.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>We have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>JOHN L. SWIFT.</item>
                            <item>WM. HENRY TRESCOT.</item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
